cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.AI, cs.DC

This paper deals with a problem related to spatial databases, specifically the MaxRS problem. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The problem involves finding the best location for a new franchise store or the most attractive place for a tourist, which suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper proposes an external-memory algorithm, which indicates that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses the optimality of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
